From: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 05:35:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: defer MLO capability advertisement

When the QCN9274 firmware advertises the MLO feature in firmware-2.bin
(features = "multi-qrtr-id,mlo"), ath12k sets ag->mlo_capable=true which
then makes mac80211 enforce the full MLO API contract on registration
(link_info_changed, AMPDU_AGGREGATION, MFP_CAPABLE, AP_LINK_PS, etc).
ath12k as shipped doesn't satisfy all of those, so ieee80211_register_hw
fails with -EINVAL and the device never comes up.

Until the driver's MLO surface is complete, mask the firmware-advertised
MLO bit so we register as a non-MLO multi-pdev driver. The dualmac AMSS
firmware still loads (its selection is independent of the MLO feature
bit) and both PHYs come up as separate wiphys / radios.

Signed-off-by: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
@@ -2152,10 +2152,16 @@ void ath12k_core_hw_group_set_mlo_capabl
 
 	if (ag->num_devices == 1) {
 		ab = ag->ab[0];
-		/* QCN9274 firmware uses firmware IE for MLO advertisement */
+		/*
+		 * Even when firmware advertises MLO via firmware-N.bin, the
+		 * upstream ath12k driver doesn't yet satisfy all of mac80211's
+		 * MLO registration requirements (link_info_changed, AP_LINK_PS,
+		 * etc), so ieee80211_register_hw fails with -EINVAL. Keep MLO
+		 * disabled until that gap is closed; the dualmac AMSS still
+		 * loads (its selection is independent of this bit).
+		 */
 		if (ab->fw.fw_features_valid) {
-			ag->mlo_capable =
-				ath12k_fw_feature_supported(ab, ATH12K_FW_FEATURE_MLO);
+			ag->mlo_capable = false;
 			return;
 		}
 
